ADD TECHNICAL INDICATORS¶

In [40]:
def get_tech_ind(data):
    data['MA7'] = data.iloc[:,4].rolling(window=7).mean()
    data['MA20'] = data.iloc[:,4].rolling(window=20).mean()

    data['MACD'] = data.iloc[:,4].ewm(span=26).mean() - data.iloc[:,1].ewm(span=12,adjust=False).mean()

    data['20SD'] = data.iloc[:, 4].rolling(20).std()
    data['upper_band'] = data['MA20'] + (data['20SD'] * 2)
    data['lower_band'] = data['MA20'] - (data['20SD'] * 2)

    data['EMA'] = data.iloc[:,4].ewm(com=0.5).mean()

    data['logmomentum'] = np.log(data.iloc[:,4] - 1)

    return data
In [41]:
def tech_ind(dataset):
    fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 8), dpi = 200)
    x_ = range(3, dataset.shape[0])
    x_ = list(dataset.index)

    ax.plot(dataset['Date'], dataset['MA7'], label='Moving Average (7 days)', color='g', linestyle='--')
    ax.plot(dataset['Date'], dataset['Close'], label='Closing Price', color='#6A5ACD')
    ax.plot(dataset['Date'], dataset['MA20'], label='Moving Average (20 days)', color='r', linestyle='-.')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter("%Y"))
    plt.title('Technical indicators')
    plt.ylabel('Close (USD)')
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.legend()

    plt.show()

def normalize_data(df, range, target_column):

    '''
    df: dataframe object
    range: type tuple -> (lower_bound, upper_bound)
        lower_bound: int
        upper_bound: int
    target_column: type str -> should reflect closing price of stock
    '''

    target_df_series = pd.DataFrame(df[target_column])
    data = pd.DataFrame(df.iloc[:, :])

    X_scaler2 = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=range)
    y_scaler2 = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=range)
    X_scaler2.fit(data)
    y_scaler2.fit(target_df_series)

    X_scale_dataset2 = X_scaler2.fit_transform(data)
    y_scale_dataset2 = y_scaler2.fit_transform(target_df_series)
    
    dump(X_scaler2, open('X_scaler2.pk2', 'wb'))
    dump(y_scaler2, open('y_scaler2.pk2', 'wb'))

    return (X_scale_dataset2,y_scale_dataset2)
In [202]:
def batch_data(x_data,y_data, batch_size, predict_period):
    X_batched, y_batched, yc = list(), list(), list()

    for i in range(0,len(x_data),1):
        x_value = x_data[i: i + batch_size][:, :]
        y_value = y_data[i + batch_size: i + batch_size + predict_period][:, 0]
        yc_value = y_data[i: i + batch_size][:, :]
        if len(x_value) == batch_size and len(y_value) == predict_period:
            X_batched.append(x_value)
            y_batched.append(y_value)
            yc.append(yc_value)

    return np.array(X_batched), np.array(y_batched), np.array(yc)

def split_train_test(data):
    train_size = len(data) - 20

    return data_train, data_test

def make_generator_model(input_dim2, output_dim2, feature_size2):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential([LSTM(units = 1024, return_sequences = True, 
                                    input_shape=(input_dim2, feature_size2),recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 512, return_sequences = True, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 256, return_sequences = True, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 128, return_sequences = True, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 64, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               Dense(32),
                               Dense(16),
                               Dense(8),
                               Dense(units=output_dim2)])
    return model
In [208]:
def make_discriminator_model(input_dim2):
    cnn_net = tf.keras.Sequential()
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(8, input_shape=(input_dim2+1, 1), kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(16, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(32, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(64, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(128, kernel_size=1, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    
    cnn_net.add(LeakyReLU())
    cnn_net.add(Dense(220, use_bias=False))
    cnn_net.add(LeakyReLU())
    cnn_net.add(Dense(220, use_bias=False, activation='relu'))
    cnn_net.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
    return cnn_net
In [209]:
def discriminator_loss(real_output2, fake_output2):
    loss_f2 = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
    real_loss2 = loss_f2(tf.ones_like(real_output2), real_output2)
    fake_loss2 = loss_f2(tf.zeros_like(fake_output2), fake_output2)
    total_loss2 = real_loss2 + fake_loss2
    return total_loss2

def generator_loss(fake_output2):
    loss_f2 = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
    loss2 = loss_f2(tf.ones_like(fake_output2), fake_output2)
    return loss2
In [210]:
@tf.function

def train_step(real_x2, real_y2, yc2, generator2, discriminator2, g_optimizer2, d_optimizer2):
    with tf.GradientTape() as gen_tape2, tf.GradientTape() as disc_tape:
        generated_data2 = generator2(real_x2, training=True)
        generated_data_reshape2 = tf.reshape(generated_data2, [generated_data2.shape[0], generated_data2.shape[1], 1])
        d_fake_input = tf.concat([tf.cast(generated_data_reshape2, tf.float64), yc2], axis=1)
        real_y_reshape2 = tf.reshape(real_y2, [real_y2.shape[0], real_y2.shape[1], 1])
        d_real_input = tf.concat([real_y_reshape2, yc2], axis=1)

        real_output2 = discriminator2(d_real_input, training=True)
        fake_output2 = discriminator2(d_fake_input, training=True)

        g_loss2 = generator_loss(fake_output2)
        disc_loss2 = discriminator_loss(real_output2, fake_output2)

    gradients_of_generator2 = gen_tape2.gradient(g_loss2, generator2.trainable_variables)
    gradients_of_discriminator2 = disc_tape.gradient(disc_loss2, discriminator2.trainable_variables)

    g_optimizer2.apply_gradients(zip(gradients_of_generator2, generator2.trainable_variables))
    d_optimizer2.apply_gradients(zip(gradients_of_discriminator2, discriminator2.trainable_variables))

    return real_y2, generated_data2, {'d_loss': disc_loss2, 'g_loss2': g_loss2}

def train(real_x2, real_y2, yc2, Epochs2, generator2, discriminator2, g_optimizer2, d_optimizer2, checkpoint = 50):
    train_info = {}
    train_info["discriminator_loss"] = []
    train_info["generator_loss"] = []

    for epoch in tqdm(range(Epochs2)):
        real_price2, fake_price2, loss2 = train_step(real_x2, real_y2, yc2, generator2, discriminator2, g_optimizer2, d_optimizer2)
        G_losses2 = []
        D_losses2 = []
        Real_price2 = []
        Predicted_price2 = []
        D_losses2.append(loss2['d_loss'].numpy())
        G_losses2.append(loss2['g_loss2'].numpy())
        Predicted_price2.append(fake_price2.numpy())
        Real_price2.append(real_price2.numpy())

        if (epoch + 1) % checkpoint == 0:
            tf.keras.models.save_model(generator2, f'./models_gan/{stock_name2}/generator_V_%d.h5' % epoch)
            tf.keras.models.save_model(discriminator2, f'./models_gan/{stock_name2}/discriminator_V_%d.h5' % epoch)
            print('epoch', epoch + 1, 'discriminator_loss', loss2['d_loss'].numpy(), 'generator_loss', loss2['g_loss2'].numpy())
    
        train_info["discriminator_loss"].append(D_losses2)
        train_info["generator_loss"].append(G_losses2)
  
    Predicted_price2 = np.array(Predicted_price2)
    Predicted_price2 = Predicted_price2.reshape(Predicted_price2.shape[1], Predicted_price2.shape[2])
    Real_price2 = np.array(Real_price2)
    Real_price2 = Real_price2.reshape(Real_price2.shape[1], Real_price2.shape[2])

    plt.subplot(2,1,1)
    plt.plot(train_info["discriminator_loss"], label='Disc_loss', color='#000000')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.ylabel('Discriminator Loss')
    plt.legend()

    plt.subplot(2,1,2)
    plt.plot(train_info["generator_loss"], label='Gen_loss', color='#000000')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.ylabel('Generator Loss')
    plt.legend()

    plt.show()

    return Predicted_price2, Real_price2, np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Real_price2, Predicted_price2)) / np.mean(Real_price2)

def normalize_data(df, range, target_column):

    '''
    df: dataframe object
    range: type tuple -> (lower_bound, upper_bound)
        lower_bound: int
        upper_bound: int
    target_column: type str -> should reflect closing price of stock
    '''

    target_df_series = pd.DataFrame(df[target_column])
    data = pd.DataFrame(df.iloc[:, :])

    X_scaler3 = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=range)
    y_scaler3 = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=range)
    X_scaler3.fit(data)
    y_scaler3.fit(target_df_series)

    X_scale_dataset3 = X_scaler3.fit_transform(data)
    y_scale_dataset3 = y_scaler3.fit_transform(target_df_series)
    
    dump(X_scaler3, open('X_scaler3.pk3', 'wb'))
    dump(y_scaler3, open('y_scaler3.pk3', 'wb'))

    return (X_scale_dataset3,y_scale_dataset3)
In [223]:
def batch_data(x_data,y_data, batch_size, predict_period):
    X_batched, y_batched, yc = list(), list(), list()

    for i in range(0,len(x_data),1):
        x_value = x_data[i: i + batch_size][:, :]
        y_value = y_data[i + batch_size: i + batch_size + predict_period][:, 0]
        yc_value = y_data[i: i + batch_size][:, :]
        if len(x_value) == batch_size and len(y_value) == predict_period:
            X_batched.append(x_value)
            y_batched.append(y_value)
            yc.append(yc_value)

    return np.array(X_batched), np.array(y_batched), np.array(yc)

def split_train_test(data):
    train_size = len(data) - 20
    data_train = data[0:train_size]
    data_test = data[train_size:]
    return data_train, data_test

    train_predict_index3 = dataset3.iloc[batch_size: X_train3.shape[0] + batch_size + prediction_period3, :].index
    test_predict_index3 = dataset3.iloc[X_train3.shape[0] + batch_size:, :].index

    return train_predict_index3, test_predict_index3

def make_generator_model(input_dim3, output_dim3, feature_size3):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential([LSTM(units = 1024, return_sequences = True, 
                                    input_shape=(input_dim3, feature_size3),recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 512, return_sequences = True, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 256, return_sequences = True, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 128, return_sequences = True, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               LSTM(units = 64, recurrent_dropout = 0.3),
                               Dense(32),
                               Dense(16),
                               Dense(8),
                               Dense(units=output_dim2)])
    return model

def make_discriminator_model(input_dim3):
    cnn_net = tf.keras.Sequential()
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(8, input_shape=(input_dim3+1, 1), kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(16, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(32, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(64, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    cnn_net.add(Conv1D(128, kernel_size=1, strides=2, padding='same', activation=LeakyReLU(alpha=0.01)))
    
    cnn_net.add(LeakyReLU())
    cnn_net.add(Dense(220, use_bias=False))
    cnn_net.add(LeakyReLU())
    cnn_net.add(Dense(220, use_bias=False, activation='relu'))
    cnn_net.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
    return cnn_net

def discriminator_loss(real_output3, fake_output3):
    loss_f3 = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
    real_loss3 = loss_f3(tf.ones_like(real_output3), real_output3)
    fake_loss3 = loss_f3(tf.zeros_like(fake_output3), fake_output3)
    total_loss3 = real_loss3 + fake_loss3
    return total_loss3

def generator_loss(fake_output3):
    loss_f3 = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
    loss3 = loss_f3(tf.ones_like(fake_output3), fake_output3)
    return loss3

@tf.function

def train_step(real_x3, real_y3, yc3, generator3, discriminator3, g_optimizer3, d_optimizer3):
    with tf.GradientTape() as gen_tape3, tf.GradientTape() as disc_tape:
        generated_data3 = generator3(real_x3, training=True)
        generated_data_reshape3 = tf.reshape(generated_data3, [generated_data3.shape[0], generated_data3.shape[1], 1])
        d_fake_input = tf.concat([tf.cast(generated_data_reshape3, tf.float64), yc3], axis=1)
        real_y_reshape3 = tf.reshape(real_y3, [real_y3.shape[0], real_y3.shape[1], 1])
        d_real_input = tf.concat([real_y_reshape3, yc3], axis=1)

        real_output3 = discriminator3(d_real_input, training=True)
        fake_output3 = discriminator3(d_fake_input, training=True)

        g_loss3 = generator_loss(fake_output3)
        disc_loss3 = discriminator_loss(real_output3, fake_output3)

    gradients_of_generator3 = gen_tape3.gradient(g_loss3, generator3.trainable_variables)
    gradients_of_discriminator3 = disc_tape.gradient(disc_loss3, discriminator3.trainable_variables)

    g_optimizer3.apply_gradients(zip(gradients_of_generator3, generator3.trainable_variables))
    d_optimizer3.apply_gradients(zip(gradients_of_discriminator3, discriminator3.trainable_variables))

    return real_y3, generated_data3, {'d_loss': disc_loss3, 'g_loss3': g_loss3}

def train(real_x3, real_y3, yc3, Epochs3, generator3, discriminator3, g_optimizer3, d_optimizer3, checkpoint = 50):
    train_info = {}
    train_info["discriminator_loss"] = []
    train_info["generator_loss"] = []

    for epoch in tqdm(range(Epochs3)):
        real_price3, fake_price3, loss3 = train_step(real_x3, real_y3, yc3, generator3, discriminator3, g_optimizer3, d_optimizer3)
        G_losses3 = []
        D_losses3 = []
        Real_price3 = []
        Predicted_price3 = []
        D_losses3.append(loss3['d_loss'].numpy())
        G_losses3.append(loss3['g_loss3'].numpy())
        Predicted_price3.append(fake_price3.numpy())
        Real_price3.append(real_price3.numpy())

        if (epoch + 1) % checkpoint == 0:
            tf.keras.models.save_model(generator3, f'./models_gan/{stock_name3}/generator_V_%d.h5' % epoch)
            tf.keras.models.save_model(discriminator3, f'./models_gan/{stock_name3}/discriminator_V_%d.h5' % epoch)
            print('epoch', epoch + 1, 'discriminator_loss', loss3['d_loss'].numpy(), 'generator_loss', loss3['g_loss3'].numpy())
    
        train_info["discriminator_loss"].append(D_losses3)
        train_info["generator_loss"].append(G_losses3)
  
    Predicted_price3 = np.array(Predicted_price3)
    Predicted_price3 = Predicted_price3.reshape(Predicted_price3.shape[1], Predicted_price3.shape[2])
    Real_price3 = np.array(Real_price3)
    Real_price3 = Real_price3.reshape(Real_price3.shape[1], Real_price3.shape[2])

    plt.subplot(2,1,1)
    plt.plot(train_info["discriminator_loss"], label='Disc_loss', color='#000000')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.ylabel('Discriminator Loss')
    plt.legend()

    plt.subplot(2,1,2)
    plt.plot(train_info["generator_loss"], label='Gen_loss', color='#000000')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.ylabel('Generator Loss')
    plt.legend()

    plt.show()

    return Predicted_price3, Real_price3, np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Real_price3, Predicted_price3)) / np.mean(Real_price3)
